  "query": "How does the evidence for using acoustic devices to reduce human-wildlife conflict at aquaculture systems compare to their use on fishing gear?",
  "relevant_summary": "Across six studies at aquaculture systems, four found reduced predation on caged fish or fewer seal approaches when acoustic devices were used at salmon/fin-fish farms, while two found no reduction in harbour seal predation or dolphin presence/behaviour around farms [2775]. On fishing gear, 33 studies collectively reported multiple behavioural effects and bycatch outcomes, and specifically five of six conflict-focused studies found reduced damage to catches and/or nets by dolphins and seals, with one study finding no reduction in swordfish catch damage by California sea lions [2808]. An additional study using acoustic decoys to divert whales from fishing lines found that placing the decoy further from lines resulted in fewer sperm whales at the lines, although whale presence and time of arrival did not differ [2820].",
